TEXT(beginproblem()); # standard preamble to each problem.


$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$p1 = random(2,3,1);
$p2 = random($p1+1,4,1);
$a = random(50,100,10);
$sum = $p1 + $p2;
$c = random(2,7,1);

$all_p = $sum-$c;
$ans = "($a)^($c/$all_p)";

BEGIN_TEXT
Question 25:
$BR $SPACE $BR
Find the EXACT solution to the equation below $BITALIC (do not give a decimal approximation)${EITALIC}.
$BR
$SPACE
$BR
\( \displaystyle \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \frac{ \log{(x^{$p1})} + \log{(x^{$p2})} }{ \log{($a x)}} = $c \) $BR $SPACE $BR
\( x = \) \{ ans_rule(35) \}
$BR

END_TEXT

ANS(num_cmp( $ans,tol=>0.000000000001 ) );

$cp3 = $c*$p3;

SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$BR $SPACE $BR 
$BBOLD  SOLUTION $EBOLD
$BR 
First we can multiply both sides by \( \log{($a x)} \) and get: $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \log{(x^{$p1})} + \log{(x^{$p2})} = $c \ \log{($a x)} \) $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \log{(x^{$p1+$p2})} = $c \ \log{($a x)} \) $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \log{(x^{$sum})} = \log{ \left( ($a x)^{$c} \right) } \) $BR
Now we can exponentiate both sides and we get the following equation which we solve for $BITALIC x${EITALIC}: $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ \ x^{$sum} = ($a x)^{$c} \) $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ \ x^{$sum} = ($a)^{$c} x^{$c} \) $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \frac{x^{$sum}}{x^{$c}} = ($a)^{$c} \) $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ \ x^{($sum - $c)} = ($a)^{$c} \) $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ \ x^{$all_p} = ($a)^{$c} \) $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ \ x = ($a)^{$c/$all_p} \)
$BR
END_SOLUTION


ENDDOCUMENT();   # This should be the last executable line in the problem.